Package: iDOM
Title: Analysis Tools of Dissolved Organic Matter Characterized by High-Resolution Mass Spectrometry
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Jianjun", "Wang", email = "jjwang@niglas.ac.cn", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Ang", "Hu", role = "aut"),
    person("Fanfan", "Meng", role = "aut")
  )
Description: Provides statistical analysis and visualization tools for dissolved organic matter characterized by high-resolution mass spectrometry.
    The package's key features include basic analyses, such as the calculation of molecular traits, the assignment of molecular classes, and the calculation of chemical diversity and dissimilarity. 
    It also offers advanced analyses to quantify the assembly processes of DOM composition, the compositional-level environmental responses of DOM, the effects of dark matter, and the specialization of DOM-microbe associations. 
    Additionally, iDOM provides visualization functions, such as van Krevelen diagrams to visualize FT-ICR MS data, and composition plots to show the relative abundances of different molecular classes. 
